*From PSAS Report or from Engineer's calcs if PSAS report is absent(PIP STC01015 4.1.7.7 Table 3
*Here the maximum value in STAAD X-DIR from PSAS report between [abs(Thermal 1)+ abs(Pressure 1)], [abs(Thermal 2)+ abs(Pressure 2)] and [abs(Thermal 3)+ abs(Pressure 3)] are input here
*Like above, in Staad Y & Z-directions also to be taken here.
*take Y-direction loads downward irrespective of PSAS sign convention for conservative approach
*For non stressed pipes or in the absence of PSAS follow like below on conservative side
*Sustained thermal loads assumed to be 10% of operating weight if there are more than 6 pipes in one level
*Sustained thermal loads assumed to be 20% of operating weight if there are 4 to 6 pipes in one level
*Sustained thermal loads assumed to be 30% of operating weight if there are 2 to 3 pipes in one level
*Sustained thermal loads assumed to be 40% of operating weight if there are 1 pipes in one level
*Reference: [PIP STC01015 4.1.7.7&Table 3]
