LOAD R11 LOADTYPE Wind  TITLE WL(+)Z
*If MEPCon structure is inside the building Wind load is not required, if out side below is applicable.
*Wind load on pipes in +Z direction will come here & Wind load on structure should be applied in Primary load case 33
*****Below is applicable for Wind load on Piping*****
*If PSAS report is absent, engineer may need to manual input PIPING/UTILITY/EQUIPMENT wind loads here. Refer to "Wind Load for Petrochemical and Other Industrial Facilities" to calculate wind load on PIPING/UTILITY/EQUIPMENT
*If PSAS load is positive in Z-DIR, it shall be kept as positive and other Load directions from PSAS report shall be used directly; if PSAS load is negative in Z-DIR, it shall be changed to positive and other Load directions shall be changed accordingly
*For example, in PSAS report, W(N/S)x=50 kN, W(N/S)y=-100 kN, W(N/S)z=20 kN, then the input shall be WX=50 kN, WZ=-100 kN, WY=20 kN
*Here STAAD X-DIR matches PSAS x-DIR(E/W-DIR). Z-DIR matches PSAS y-DIR(N/S-DIR). STAAD Y-DIR matches PSAS z-DIR(UP/DOWN-DIR)
*However, the user may encounter difficulties when inputting load directions. As a simplified but more conservative option, it is recommended to input the loads as positive values in lateral directions & downwards in vertical direction.
* IF ALL PIPES ARE STRESSED, GO WITH PSAS LOADING OTHERWISE CHOOSE HIGHEST DIA OF THE PIPE, CALCULATE THE WIND LOAD MANUALLY AND APPLY AT THE COLUMN BEAM JUNCTION AS A NODAL LOAD.
********Pipe 3 (Non stressed pipe)
*Here one pipe is non stressed, calculating wind load manually.
*consider largest pipe dia is 150mm+(50mm_insulation)
*Wind force(F) = Cf*Ae*Pd
*Pd = 2.97kN/m2
*Cf = 0.7 ((Table 25 IS:875 part 3-2015 ))
*Ae = (D+0.1W)*attributory span, W- width of the structure
*Ae = 200+(0.1*2000)*3000 = 1.2m2
*F = 0.7*1.2*2.97 = 2.5kN
*Staad input for Load Case R11_WL(+)Z (force unit [kN])
